install [python extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.python) - install [pylance extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemname=ms-python.vscode-pylance) - install [lsp-pyright](https://github.com/emacs-lsp/lsp-pyright) package ```elisp (use-package lsp-pyright :ensure t :hook (python-mode . (lambda () (require 'lsp-pyright) (lsp))) ; or lsp-deferred :init (when (executable-find "python3") (setq lsp-pyright-python-executable-cmd "python3")) ) ``` - make sure emacs uses the environment where you have installed `boto3-stubs` type checking should now work. no explicit type annotations required, write your `boto3` code as usual. ### sublime text - install `boto3-stubs[bedrock-agent]` mypy_boto3_bedrock_agent.type_defs import s3identifiertypedef def get_value() -> s3identifiertypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `boto3` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `boto3` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `boto3` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the `mypy-boto3-bedrock-agent` package version 1.34.7, released on December 22, 2023, available on PyPI. It provides type annotations for the `boto3.AgentsforBedrock` service, generated with `mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.0`. The package aims to enhance code completion and error detection in various IDEs (VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text) and tools (mypy, pyright) by offering explicit type annotations for `boto3` client and paginator usage. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package is developed by Vlad Emelianov and supports a wide range of Python versions from 3.8 to 3.13. Installation instructions, usage examples, and information on uninstallation are provided, emphasizing the package's compatibility and ease of integration into development workflows.
